From: William Mannheimer <ihc@swipnet.se>

I read with interest the story of bats with cleft palates. Could they have
other malformations in the brain? I believe it is very suggestive of a
virus infection -- type bluetonguevirus -- that gave the whole book of
pathology of malformations of the skull and CNS. It is also in Australia if
I remember rightly.
