[2
From: Tony Ross <tony_ross_at_emai@smtpgwy.agric.nsw.gov.au>
NSW Ag could test for neutralising antibodies to Menangle virus in affected
and unaffected animals to assist the investigation of this problem. Virus
isolation could be attempted but some funding may be necessary.
Menangle virus in pigs is a neurotrophic teratogenic paramyxovirus. We know
it is found in flying foxes but do not know what it does.

--
Tony Ross,
NSW, Australia
